<scriptment id="26000" point="umehara" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-06-29" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki, at the bar, looks to her left&#x2014;</narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Umehara?</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">Pankratova?</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">What?</line>
		<line id="4000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">You assumed I was a famous competitive gamer,</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">so I assumed you were the woman with the world's longest legs.</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">It's only fair.</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Doesn't hurt to play to win.</line>
		<line id="8000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">So what are you doing here?</line>
		<line id="9000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">Learning by observation.</line>
		<narration>Umehara points to the bartender.<comment>Yuki has the player take a look too.</comment>The tender, with acrobatic motion in an unscripted ocean, shepherds bottles to their places and items to their cases, every delicate touch contributing to a glass gliding from man to man.</narration>

		<line id="10000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">Devastation, Evolution, Tougeki&#x2014; all canceled.</comment>
		<line id="11000" speaker="umehara" voicelang="ja">Gonna lay low and try a new kind of physical challenge.</comment>
		<narration>Umehara continues to watch the bartender in action.</narration>
	</part>
</scriptment>